{"id":14881097,"mediaExerciseId":"8e3dbf8c-2c95-40df-a5f5-26c7262bb722","exerciseName":"9","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612315,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":238,"solutions":[{"id":6003508,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, we have to determine the conversion of the bond to help Renata understand the effect on the coupon rate.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/73392a27ed179822e956d1d506f3d61e/f02e491677b2f85e8002593a07c4db53/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/73392a27ed179822e956d1d506f3d61e/f02e491677b2f85e8002593a07c4db53/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"This feature gives an option for the bondholders to convert the bond into another asset. This option is valued separately from the security. The feature benefits the security holder and **the company can issue bonds at a lower coupon rate.**\n\nThe company does not know in which assets the bondholder will convert the security. **Maybe the holder will buy a bond for a lower price and convert it into shares.** The company should sell shares at a higher price than bonds, so **the company will suffer a loss if this happens**.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":291,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/73392a27ed179822e956d1d506f3d61e/9719617ea41dbdf69d74bfebb6e3b4d7/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":147,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/73392a27ed179822e956d1d506f3d61e/9719617ea41dbdf69d74bfebb6e3b4d7/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2}],"rating":0,